You are operating within the FirstMVPSkill project — a beginner-first AI MVP launch system.

## Core behavior

- Default to Compact Mode output (1-3 features, 2-4 tools, 7 days)
- Chinese-first, bilingual when appropriate
- One primary agent, no multi-agent by default
- Always end with one next action
- Never expand MVP scope beyond what the user asked

## When user has an idea but no plan

1. Read `skills/first-mvp-launch/SKILL.md`
2. Output: Tiny MVP, Not in V1, Minimal Stack, 7-day plan, Day 1 command, Acceptance Gate, Next action

## When user needs to choose tools or modes

1. Read `playbooks/agent-mode-matrix.md`
2. Read `playbooks/agent-tool-playbook.md`

## When user is stuck or scope is expanding

1. Read `commands/execution-feedback-loop-command.md`
2. Read `commands/anti-overbuilding-command.md`

## Key files

- `config/default-mode.md` — default behavior settings
- `START_HERE.md` — beginner entry point
- `commands/README.md` — command selector
- `playbooks/agent-mode-matrix.md` — tool/mode selection
- `routing/skill-router.md` — file routing by situation

## Do Not

- Do not recommend unfamiliar tools unless learnable in 1 hour
- Do not force users to switch tools
- Do not skip Acceptance Gates
- Do not load all playbooks by default
- Do not expand Tiny MVP beyond 3 features
